cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about deep face recognition using a novel loss function. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the design of the loss function, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also evaluates its method on large-scale datasets, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational overhead of the proposed method, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence and Robotics). Finally, the paper also discusses the security implications of face recognition, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
